questions.answer:
Implement per-tenant isolation with dedicated service accounts and IAM bindings using per-tenant Cloud Run revision tags for traffic splitting. Create per-tenant VPC Service Controls perimeters with Cloud Run in the service perimeter to restrict data exfiltration. Provision per-tenant Pub/Sub topics and assign Dataflow flex templates with least-privilege IAM roles.

Use Cloud Deploy with a YAML-based deployment configuration to define per-tenant traffic percentages (e.g., 10% v3, 90% v2), achieving zero-downtime progressive rollout. Apply revision tags (tenant-a-v3, tenant-b-v3) and configure the Load Balancer to route traffic based on these tags.

Configure Cloud Monitoring SLI dashboards for per-tenant latency (p99 < 500ms) and error rate (5xx < 0.1%). Set up Cloud Monitoring alerting policies that trigger Cloud Deploy rollback commands via Cloud Build triggers or Cloud Scheduler when SLIs breach thresholds for more than 5 minutes.

Use Terraform to provision per-tenant resources:
```hcl
resource "google_service_account" "tenant_a" {
  account_id   = "tenant-a-sa"
  display_name = "Tenant A Service Account"
}

resource "google_pubsub_topic" "tenant_a_events" {
  name = "tenant-a-events"
}

resource "google_cloud_run_service_iam_member" "tenant_a_invoker" {
  service  = google_cloud_run_service.default.name
  region   = google_cloud_run_service.default.location
  role     = "roles/run.invoker"
  member   = "serviceAccount:tenant-a-sa@${var.project_id}.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
}
```

Apply the principle of least privilege with roles/run.invoker rather than roles/run.admin for tenant service accounts.

