## Why This Is Asked
This assesses practical setup of observability and cost controls using native GCP tools without reliance on third-party services.

## Key Concepts
- Cloud Run autoscaling tuning and resource requests
- Cloud Monitoring custom metrics and dashboards
- Artifact Registry and Cloud Build deployment
- Billing budgets and alerting
- Least-privilege IAM for deployment

## Code Example
```javascript
// Node.js snippet to emit a custom metric to Cloud Monitoring
const {MetricServiceClient} = require('@google-cloud/monitoring');
const client = new MetricServiceClient();
async function publishRPSS(sps) {
  const dataPoint = {
    value: {doubleValue: sps}
  };
  const timeSeries = {
    metric: {type: 'custom.googleapis.com/requests_per_second'},
    resource: {type: 'global', labels: {project_id: process.env.GCP_PROJECT}},
    points: [{interval: {endTime: {seconds: Date.now()/1000}}, value: dataPoint}]
  };
  await client.createTimeSeries({name: client.projectPath(process.env.GCP_PROJECT), timeSeries: [timeSeries]});
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test the alert policy and validate no false positives?
- How would you scale this across many environments while maintaining least privilege?

